#Repost @harmonycolumbus  "Human trafficking isn't exclusive to big events, it's happening 365 days a year."  Judge Paul Herbert started the CATCH (Changing Actions To Change Habits) Court in 2009 here in Columbus in response to an overwhelming number of domestic violence and prostitution cases coming before the court. As he educated himself on the subject, he found the issue, in part, was rooted in early childhood domestic sexual abuse.   The thought that women sell their bodies because they are addicted to drugs is not the truth. Victims of early childhood sexual abuse experience trauma that makes them more susceptible to drugs and further victimization from men all around the world looking to make money off of them.   1/3 of women in prostitution start before they are 15 years old. 66% start before their 18th birthday. For women who have entered CATCH Court, the average age for when they first faced sexual abuse is 8.5 years old.   "If you have a child, make sure you know what they're doing on their cell phone. Cell phones are the number 1 tool used to lure kids into situations that lead to trafficking."  Today is #HumanTraffickingAwarenessDay.

Often labor trafficking victims enter the US legally on temporary work visas. They are then forced into labor under the guise of legal employment.  Agricultural, hospitality, domestic service, construction, and restaurants are common fields where people can be exploited. Temporary work visas are often tied to a single employer, if the person leaves that employer, they can be deported. Deportation is a threat used by traffickers to maintain control over their victims. #labor #trafficking

message: In October of 2020, the first memorial dedicated to survivors of sex trafficking was unveiled in Kansas City, Missouri. The art installation, "Into the Light", located at Lykins Square Park was created by glass artist and sculptor, Hasna Sal.  While traveling, one of ERASE's team members had the opportunity to meet the artist and view the memorial.   Not only is the memorial beautifully done but it also creates an awareness about sex trafficking for the people visiting the park. We need to see more of these around the country.   We are very grateful that Hasna used her talents to not only raise awareness about sex trafficking but to give a glimpse of the path that individuals victimized by sex trafficking often endure.  To learn more, follow Hasna's IG account. @hasnasalofficial   #artofinstagram #sculpture #glassartist #artforgood #helpERASE #ChildTrafficking #kansascity #travel #parks #neighborhood #makingadifference

Awareness is key! Thank you @danicamckellar Yesterday was #WorldDayAgainstTrafficking... people wore blue and posted about modern day slavery. For several hours I read and researched and also talked to my good friend @jenlilley who is a foster mom and strong advocate for children. Yesterday was my day for learning, so I could post today... Let's shine a light on this multi-billion dollar (and the fastest growing) criminal industry in the world - and increasing at an even faster pace because of our lockdown response to the pandemic. I'm not going to go into detail about what happens to these slaves, but it's devastating, and about a third of them are children. And more than you'd think is happening right here in the U.S., some hiding in plain sight.  [pensive]  . It's not comfortable to think about, but heck, nothing in 2020 feels comfortable anyway, so why not educate ourselves and be a positive force?? . Once upon a time, slavery was legal in this country. So many citizens chose to ignore the devastation happening right in front of them. . Let's not be those people who chose to ignore slavery because it's uncomfortable. Modern day slavery is real, it's horrific, and needs our attention and advocacy.  . What can we do?  . Awareness: We can follow accounts like @ourrescue, @a21, @helperase, @uheroes, @thorn and more, to become aware and familiar *over time* and to see the heroic work they are doing - leave them comments, periodically share their posts with your followers... they will truly appreciate your involvement! . Volunteer: Foster kids without a positive force in their lives are *far* more likely to become victims of trafficking. Becoming a child advocate for a foster child through CASA (link in bio) is an incredible gift, as is mentoring a high-risk child through a program like @bgcaclubs or @bbbsamerica. These are the most valuable and heroic acts you could take, aside from actually becoming a foster parent.  [redheart]  . Donate: Of course, all of these organizations are working hard and donations keep them going! . If you've taken the time to read all of this, THANK YOU from the bottom of my heart. And thank you in advance for any of the above items you choose to do.

#Repost @repchrissmith  Today, we recognize #WorldDayAgainstHumanTrafficking, a day to raise awareness and redouble our efforts to protect weak and vulnerable populations from sex or labor trafficking. Human trafficking is a barbaric human rights abuse that thrives on greed, secrecy, a perverted sense of entitlement to exploit the vulnerable and an unimaginable disregard for the victims. As the author of five comprehensive laws to combat human trafficking--including the landmark Trafficking Victims Protection Act (TVPA)-which marks 20 years of success this year-- I urge everyone to redouble their efforts and step up, bolster, and renew our commitment to eradicate the scourge of human trafficking once and for all.  Unfortunately, COVID-19 has made our anti-human trafficking work more challenging-especially as predators groom more children online, traffickers and those they exploit become even more invisible, and jobs evaporate for rescued victims making them more susceptible to being trafficked.  You can help break the cycle of human trafficking.   Call the National Human Trafficking Hotline: 1-888-373-7888 if you or someone you know is a victim of human trafficking or to report a tip on suspected trafficking activity.  #endhumantrafficking #humanrights #trafficking

Working alongside dedicated individuals on the front lines in the fight against trafficking is how ERASE makes a difference. We work endlessly to provide victim-centered & trauma-informed services to individuals who have been trafficked.  "Committed to the Cause - Working on the Frontline to End Human Trafficking" The UN's theme for #WDATIP this year, is to highlight the first responders to human trafficking. These are the people who work in different sectors - identifying, supporting, counseling, and seeking justice for victims of trafficking, and challenging the impunity of the traffickers.  #EndHumanTrafficking #HumanTrafficking

#Repost @thebrowsnobdenver  Juneteenth (a portmanteau of June and nineteenth;[2] also known as Freedom Day,[3] Jubilee Day,[4] and Liberation Day[5]) started as a Texas state holiday, but is now celebrated annually on the 19th of June throughout the United States to commemorate Union army general Gordon Granger announcing federal orders in the city of Galveston, Texas, on June 19, 1865, proclaiming that all slaves in Texas were now free.[6] Although the Emancipation Proclamation had formally freed them almost two and a half years earlier and the American Civil War had largely ended with the defeat of the Confederate States in April, Texas was the most remote of the slave states, with a low presence of Union troops, so enforcement of the proclamation had been slow and inconsistent.**** Wikipedia. #junteenth #freedomday

Authorities rescued a 17-year-old human trafficking victim in San Bernardino, according to the San Bernardino County Sheriff's Department. On May 21 at about 3 p.m., investigators from the San Bernardino County Human Trafficking Task Force received information from the Redlands Police Department regarding a female juvenile being exploited at a local motel. The juvenile, who was being advertised for prostitution in an online ad that was several days old, was identified as a recent runaway from Riverside County. Investigators continued searching for the victim and at about 4 a.m. the next day, they received information that she had been seen near Colton. Investigators ultimately located the victim near Interstate 215 and University Parkway in San Bernardino. She was provided access to services and safely released to her family.  #childtrafficking #teen #runaway #vulnerablechildren

#Repost @helperase  "I was important to recover because I was...I was not recovered because you thought I wasn't." This headline is disturbing and sad. As a non-profit that provides direct services to both minor and adult trafficking victims and provide law enforcement training, we know this is not the solution. This reinforces that police are not a safe option to turn to for help if you're a trafficking victim.  From past experience we have seen these types of operations are done because there is a lack of training and cultural understanding of human trafficking.  When agencies are provided law enforcement led training with instructors who have years of experience with HT the out come is different. The right people are arrested, (sex-buyers and traffickers) and victims or potential victims of human trafficking are provided services.  We owe it to communities to do a better job. Great work by all involved! This is a perfect example of why we have a Law Enforcement Program. ERASE provides direct services to individuals victimized by human traffickers and we know that Law Enforcement is key to getting traffickers behind bars. Law enforcement led instruction is essential in delivering the training needed by other law enforcement new to investigating human trafficking crimes. The training we have provided over the last several years was developed by instructors who have in-depth experience in working with human trafficking investigations. Additional speakers in the class have been subject matter experts on using a victim-centered/trauma-informed approach and the importance of community and family involvement. The classes we presented have made a positive impact in the neighborhoods of the attending agencies and have changed the lives of many who have been victimized by traffickers. To learn more please visit https://www.erasechildtrafficking.org/human-trafficking-training    #LEOs #InlandEmpire #MakingADifference #LawEnforcementTraining #HumanTrafficking #PoliceInvestigations

message: Karena is getting ready for the morning. We are still hoping to have 40 people to show support. @karenasteir and her daughter Mia are walking a half marathon covered in Band-Aids decorated by YOU.  Did we mention she lives in Iowa?! It's going to be cold! To donate and show support head over to our Facebook page @HelpERASE and you will see the Band-Aid Fundraiser.  This is a message from Karena.  CHILDREN LOVE BAND-AIDS They know people SEE their pain with a Band-Aid. They feel CARED for when they get a Band-Aid.  They can HEAL once they have a Band-Aid. These feelings match how we want to approach our Human Trafficking victims, survivors and conquerors. We want them to know they are SEEN, we want them to feel CARED for and we want to help them HEAL.  This year I am doing a fundraiser for ERASE Child Trafficking - a US based non-profit dedicated to educating communities, recovering victims and providing aftercare to survivors. Their vast reach and intense involvement in this field is unmatched. The ERASE team can be found nationwide training law enforement, speaking at public events, acquiring housing & transporation for survivors as well as many other behind-the-scene duties. Being a part of ERASE, I've seen first hand how far even the smallest of donations can go. A donation of $5 may buy lunch for a survivor on her first day of freedom. A donation of $10 may get him basic toiletries for his new life. A donation of $50 may get him a bus pass or basic cell phone. A donation of $100 may help her acquire a new wardrobe. A donation of $425 pays for the full training of a law enforcement individual learning the lastest tips, technology and mindsets in the fight against Human Trafficking.  This year I'm asking for help getting victims, survivors & conquerors  SEEN, CARED FOR & HEALED.  I'm asking YOU to be a Band-Aid. My goal is to find 100 donors willing to kick in $5 (the lowest amount FB is willing to process) in an effort to show our community cares. Will you buy a $5 Band-Aid? #hiddenpain #unseen #trauma #support #LE #MakingADifference #pimplife to #lifeinjail

On National Police Woman Day we honor Detective Kim Hernandez from San Bernardino Police Department. Det. Hernandez recently joined the ERASE Child Trafficking Team.   Det. Hernandez is dedicated to making an impact on Human Trafficking.   Thank you  Det. Hernandez for your hard work.  Detective Hernandez has been a police officer with the San Bernardino Police Department since 2006. During her career, she has been assigned to the Crime Impact Team, Graffiti Task Force, the Violent Crimes Task Force, and the Vice/Narcotics Unit. In January 2016, she was assigned as the Vice Detective and began working cases involving the commercialized sex trade, including Human Trafficking, Pimping and Pandering. Some of Detective Hernandez's accomplishments include participation in over 94 operations targeting human trafficking, more than 350 criminal investigations, 325 arrests involving human trafficking, 73 felony cases filed, 236 years of state prison sentences. Most importantly 119 adults recovered and 73 juveniles recovered from human trafficking situations. In March 2017, she received the Meritorious Service Medal for her work in combating human trafficking. In 2017, she was assigned to the San Bernardino County Human Trafficking Task Force, which is managed by the San Bernardino Sheriff's Department and includes investigators from local, state, and federal agencies. In May 2018, she was nominated for Officer of the Year by the San Bernardino City Chamber of Commerce for her continued work in Human Trafficking, including successful prosecutions and training for the community and first responders. Detective Hernandez instructs at the San Bernardino Sheriff's Department's Advanced Officer Training Center, California POST, and California Narcotic Officers' Association. In August 2019 Detective Hernandez, was the recipient of The California Narcotic Officers' Association, Alfred E. Stewart Award, Region V for her distinguished and dedicated service in combating human trafficking. #sanbernardino #leo #makingadifference #nationalpolicewomanday #humantrafficking

In conjunction with Human Trafficking Awareness Month, the San Bernardino County Human Trafficking Task Force participated in the fifth annual 'Operation Reclaim and Rebuild' enforcement operation, organized by the Los Angeles Regional Human Trafficking Task Force. More than 90 federal, state and local law enforcement agencies and task forces from across California participated. The three-day, statewide effort aimed at combatting human trafficking, took place between Thursday, January 24, and Saturday, January 26, 2019, and was conducted in various mediums and met with positive results. Over the three day period, the San Bernardino County Task Force conducted enforcement operations consisting of 2-3 operational phases per day. Operations were conducted throughout the county and specifically within the cities of San Bernardino, Ontario, Rancho Cucamonga and Hesperia. Specific areas were selected for enforcement by investigators, due to the high volume of activity and advertisements directly related to the commercial sex trafficking industry. The operations consisted of street level enforcement, on-line advertisements enforcement and a search warrant served at a high desert location, determined to be a commercial brothel. At the end of the operational period, San Bernardino County Task Force members had successfully arrested 45 suspects. Of those arrests, one suspect who was contacted at an Ontario motel, was arrested for felony possession of a controlled substance while in possession of multiple and illegal firearms. During the operation, investigators also identified and successfully rescued 4 adult victims of commercial sex trafficking. https://local.nixle.com/alert/7083350/?subid=10614532  #makingadifference #endhumantrafficking #leo #helperase

A survey was conducted and revealed that the suicide rate is increasing in victims of human trafficking. That's why it's very important to recognize the link between human trafficking and suicide. Self-Injury Depression Sexually transmitted infections Posttraumatic stress disorders and anxiety disorders Suicidal thoughts A recent study found that human trafficking survivors have an alarming higher-than-average rate of suicidal thoughts with a percentage of 23% of survivors having attempted suicide, compared with 3% of the population with no prior domestic violence exposure.  If you are someone you know are experiencing suicidal thoughts, whether they are human trafficking victims are not, here are some things you can do: Be a good listener instead of being judgemental Encourage them to seek help from Psychologists and mental health professionals Help them build strong relationships with others outside of an abusive environment Help them connect with support groups and other community resources Call the Suicide Prevention Hotline listed below: The National Suicide Prevention Lifeline in the U.S at 800-273-TALK (800-273-8255) to reach a trained counselor. What makes the business of human trafficking so lucrative?  Limitless Supply Access to the Internet, Minimal social support, Poverty, Foster Care, History of Sexual Abuse, Low self-esteem, Mental Illness, Drug Addiction, Homelessness and Natural Disasters all contribute to the endless supply of victims.   High Demand Increasing demand for commercial sex - especially with young girls and boys - incentivizes commercial sex venues including strip clubs, pornography, and prostitution to recruit and exploit children. High demand drives the high volume of supply.  Huge Profit Margins Studies show that sexual exploitation can yield a return on investment ranging from 100% to 1,000%, while an enslaved laborer can produce more than 50% profit even in less profitable markets.  Big Resale Value In 2009, the average price of a slave was $90. A sex trafficking victim can be sold as many as 20-30 times a day.   Low Risk The number of Prosecutions of Human Traffickers is alarmingly low. Already burdened by increasing caseloads, prosecutors and law enforcement lack the training, time, and resources to investigate and prosecute human trafficking crimes. #NotForSale

ERASE's team member David was in Phoenix, for a screening of the I am Jane Doe Film hosted by The McCain Institute and StreetLightUSA.  I Am Jane Doe intertwines the true stories of several teenage girls fallen victim to sex trafficking with the ongoing legal battles against Backpage.com. "The film was very powerful and invoked strong emotions" stated Werba, "To see how Backpage company revenue soared upward while they not only listed but facilitated online trafficking rings...it's just a travesty that this was allowed to happen."  The victims and their families, the "Jane Doe" plaintiffs, continue to fight the men behind Backpage in court. Breakthroughs were highlighted at the end of the film, and support is rising as the truth continues to come out about this issue that affects every community in America.

Via Fargo Police Department  "FBI warns popular app for teens helps child predators go undetected  An app used to find friends has become popular among teenagers and has also caught the attention of the FBI.  The app, called Yellow, allows users to chat and share pictures.  After downloading the app, the user must enter a birth date.  The app won't allow anyone under the age of 13 to create a profile, but FBI agents said child predators are posing as teens to find victims.  Yellow is marketed as an app that can be used to make new friends who are close by.  The user swipes right if they are interested in the person, and left if they're uninterested. It's similar to the dating app Tinder and has been dubbed "Tinder for teens." "This app, as well as other apps, are definitely on our radar," said FBI Agent Kevin Kaufman."  http://www.wftv.com/news/local/fbi-warns-popular-app-for-teens-helps-child-predators-go-undetected/493102398

If you are in the LA area next week on 2/23 we are fortunate to be hosting a panel at Summit Live. This is not a normal venue for a Human Trafficking Panel. However, #SummitLive is going outside the box to give a voice to a problem that most do not want to discuss..child sex trafficking. Thanks to Summit Live and Ryan Bell we have a panel of experts from areas where human trafficking is at its worst.  The knowledge that our speakers bring to the conversation is immeasurable. We are bringing law enforcement and social media together to spread awareness about child trafficking to an audience that potentially can reach hundreds of thousands of people.   California and Florida are in the top three states with the highest incidents of human trafficking. We have speakers representing task forces from both states.  We also have a social media expert who also happens to be the founder of Summit Live and a live streamer and child advocate who is passionate about spreading awareness about child trafficking.  And bridging the gap is a law enforcement officer who specializes in training LE and other public safety professionals on how to use social media at their respective agencies.  Our panel- Cpt. Chris Marks, Captain of Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department Human Trafficking Bureau and the LA Regional Human Trafficking Task Force, SA Victor Williams, Special Agent Williams is assigned to the Office of the Special Agent in Charge Miami, Human Trafficking Group and Coordinator for the South Florida Human Trafficking Task Force, Ryan Anderson Bell  Sgt.Marc Marty & Karena Steir
message_tags: SummitLive Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department Victor Williams South Florida Human Trafficking Task Force Marc Marty Karena Steir #SummitLive

message: Fact 25 ~ For Medical Professionals A U.S. study on sex trafficking found that more than 85 percent of survivors had contact with a health care professional while being trafficked.   Spotting Signs of Sex Trafficking for Health Care Providers- Red flags in a patient's presentation and health care history that warrant further questions: poor eye contact; anxiety; a scripted or mechanically recited history; being a runaway or in the foster-care system; sexual promiscuity; recurrent STIs; multiple pregnancies; malnourishment; substance addiction; weather-inappropriate clothing; bruising, scars, or burns in hidden places; a tattoo of a pimp's name or a strange symbol; the inability to provide an address; and a companion who refuses to leave the examination room.  30 Facts ~ Human Trafficking Prevention and Awareness.   #HealthCare #EducateYourself #ProtectOurKids

Luckily these girls were able to get away. Have you talked with your children about how to stay safe?  Here are some safety tips for parents and children.   *Be aware that the most dangerous times can be just before and after school.  There is strength in numbers. Kids should walk in groups.   *Don't walk away with anyone other than a parent, or the person who was already arranged to take care of the child that day.  *Children should never approach a car or truck no matter what the occupants say. Remember, an adult does not need help from a child - not to find a puppy, not for anything. If an adult is asking for help, that's a warning sign.  *Avoid getting into a car with a stranger at all costs. Children should stay on sidewalks or at least six feet from the street.  *Know the rules: what is OK and what is not OK, and have confidence to take action if they feel someone is trying to take advantage of them.  *If someone grabs them, they should scream and yell out "HELP ME -- CALL THE POLICE."  *When children think they see danger, they should run and tell an adult immediately.

message: As we leave Social Media Week Miami we can't stop smiling... It's something that we don't do as much as we like. Our work can be emotional and, quite bluntly, sad.  The friends and partners we made like the City of Miami Police Department and The Department of Homeland Security give us promise and builds hope in our hearts. We go home knowing that in some small way we've brought the world together. Thanks to everyone who loves us, shares us and donates to our cause. It's a hard one... but it's a good one and we're not afraid to smile while we work.   Smiling means that we know we are making a difference.   Thank you for your help, ~Sandy & Ryan #HelpErase

Join Ryan A Bell, Dave Werba and Lizza Monet Morales as they discuss how social media is being used to help eliminate child trafficking.  This is a preview to next week's Social Media Week Miami.  Social Media and VR in the Fight Against Child Trafficking;  A discussion how social media and child trafficking are intertwined. As a taboo subject, this initiative has historically seen low engagement and few shares. By utilizing influencers, live streaming and creating an "empathy machine" through storytelling in virtual reality, Erase Child Trafficking is pioneering the use of Social VR as a movement. Social media experts discuss how they are working to reach the masses to educate parents and teens, and how to create a multimedia story for social good.  #FacebookLive broadcast and production provided by Enlightened Audiovisual from their #Brandroom Studio in Gaithersburg, MD.

We know that in order to make an impact on Child Trafficking we can not do it alone, it will have to be a collaborative effort. Yesterday's live stream was an example of that collaboration.  We greatly appreciate the community that has joined in the fight against child trafficking.

Luckily this young boy's father was able to catch the abductor and the child is safe. Parents it can happen in the blink of the eye.  Role-play with your children to help them learn how to respond to risky situations.  Have children practice yelling, "You're not my Mom/DAD", kicking, pulling away or otherwise attracting attention when grabbed or approached by an unknown person.
With little hope for a way to provide for their families Romanian girls are at high risk for being trafficked in Europe.  http://bit.ly/2b4emyP
#TheWorldNeedsMore #Hope that we can #endchildtrafficking. #WorldHumanitarianDay
Big Win in the fight against Internet Crimes Against Children. New Jersey State Police has done a great job in protecting our kids. Thank you!
We have to understand the weapons our enemies use in order to properly fight them.

We couldn't be more excited to be teaming up with Zeality, VRSalon, 1WorldNow Media, and others in VR to create content that will help educate and spread awareness about Child Trafficking. We need your help. ERASE's mission is to be a unifying voice creating a cultural shift in the perception of child trafficking, working towards its eradication by empowering action against this inhumanity through education, recovery, and life reclamation.  Raising funds to be able to do these things is crucial. We are asking that you click the "Donate Now" button to #HelpErase #ChildTrafficking. Thank you for your support!   https://youtu.be/HvrhLTF51KI

46 Kids a day go missing in the US  Average lifespan of a trafficked child is 7 years  Average age child enters into the sex trade is 11-14  We can keep reading about the statistics  OR  We can start changing the statistics.  Visit HelpErase.org for more information

We are still coming across videos that were part of our #HelpErase awareness campaign. We missed this video from our friends at Summit Live. Cathy Hackl shares a story from when she was a journalist and talked with a trafficking victim.  The story may be hard to hear but it is one of thousands across the US. People may think it is rare for an American teenager to be trafficked from the US to another country but unfortunately, it isn't. 46 kids a day going missing in the US. Please #HelpErase #ChildTrafficking
This is a beautiful way to shine a light of the problem of child trafficking. Thank you.

"Victim-blaming is never an accurate or appropriate response when it comes to dealing with sex trafficking survivors" said Jeffery Mayfield, the Homeland Security Investigations Resident Agent in Charge for Amarillo.

Another great job! 23 children were recovered by Tulare County Sheriff's Office during Operation Baby Face. Again this is another example that child trafficking is happening in our own backyards. If you see something suspicious or think a child might be involved in a trafficking situation please report it to local law enforcements.  #helperase #childtrafficking

People are often amazed that human trafficking happens in their own back yard, not to mention child trafficking.  The numbers below reflect how big of a problem it is. Congratulations to the Cook County Sheriff's Office and other departments who participated in multi state arrests focused on the buyers.   71 sex trafficking arrests 1,358 sex solicitation arrests (johns) More than $1 million in fines More than 1,300 charges (felony, misdemeanor and ordinance violations) 58 adult victims recovered/offered services ****32 juvenile victims recovered**** 2,015 johns deterred (includes texts, calls and webpage re-directs to inform sex buyers of the harmful impact of the sex industry) 421 vehicles towed/impounded/seized 60 percent of arrests stemmed from online advertisements, of which 99 percent were from Backpage.  http://bit.ly/2bi7luf
"A Society's Destiny Rest on How It Treats It's Children." #helperase #childtrafficking.
A brilliant use of technology (augmented reality in this case) to tell a story.

Volusia County Sheriff's Office and several other law enforcement agencies arrested 13 men who thought they were headed to meet a teenager for sex. Hats off to Volusia County Sheriff's Office for the arrest and for posting the names of these men. Great job! #helperase #childtrafficking
A win in Tennessee -14 arrested were involved in human trafficking.
Tennessee Bureau of Investigation doing an outstanding job of getting the bad guys off the street. #helperase #childtrafficking
This is just one of many stories that non profits working to end child trafficking have to tell. We as a society have to do better. These children are the future...we can't let them down.
Identification is one of the most important parts of education.

For many survivors, once removed from a trafficking situation another set of problems begin. The amount of survivors vs the amount of services offered to them is extremely unbalanced. Survivors need specialized care and treatment, without it they are very likely to end up back in a trafficking situation. These survivors deserve better treatment options.
Happy to see the NY Gov on top of this so quickly hopefully, other states will follow his lead. We need to do everything we can to protect our kids.
Awesome job by Tennessee Bureau of Investigation in recovering missing 12 year old from TX.
Thank you Stephanie! pic.twitter.com/iMQYNJiIDm

We are so grateful for the many video submissions we have been getting. Please take a moment and scroll through the page to see all the help we are receiving to Erase Child Trafficking. This is a great submission from Covered Cubs. Thank you! #helperase #igivehope

A Great video submission for our #helperase awareness challenge! Thank you Larry!
A fun contribution to the #helperase  awareness challenge from one of our senior team members.

When talking human trafficking statistics people can sometimes forget each number represents a life. #helperase #childtrafficking  http://www.erasechildtrafficking.org/statistics-of-human-trafficking/
Here is another great video for our #HelpErase campaign. Thank you Catherine.
This is a submission for the #helperase awareness challenge. We are excited to see what you are doing.
"I have hope as a survivor and an advocate that we can end human trafficking" Ima Matul opening eyes on human trafficking in the US tonight. http://bit.ly/2akvLS3

We are doing an awareness campaign to shed light on the growing problem of child trafficking. July 30th is World Day Against Trafficking in Persons and we are asking for your help.   Take Action with a video or picture showing the words "Child Trafficking" being physically erased.  Then post the video or picture to social media using the hashtag #HelpErase. Your online voice can make a difference!   http://www.erasechildtrafficking.org/world-day-against-trafficking-in-persons/

Sending child sex trafficking victims  to juvenile detention centers is like victimizing them all over again says Sandy Middleton, executive director of Center for Violence Prevention. http://buff.ly/2aFj7dI #childtrafficking
We are resharing this #missing poster. The young girl was last seen in the Hillsborough County, Fl area. We are asking people to please share. #Tampa, #Pasco, #Florida

While there is a higher percentage of women involved in human trafficking, boys and young men are at risk as well. Males are less likely to seek help. The Metropolitan Organization to Counter Sexual Assault in Kansas City is trying to change that through offering services to males who have been sexually exploited.  http://bit.ly/2aD3O52
"Sex offenders in our community used to go to parks and playgrounds  now they go on the Internet," Officer Gary Oriet said. "It's scary to think about." http://buff.ly/2aoec0t #childtrafficking

"As with many youth-related issues, teachers are a first line of defense. The U.S. Department of Education says schools should look for students who lack control over their schedule, have unexplained absences, show signs of physical trauma and have seemingly rehearsed answers to questions."  http://buff.ly/29QkTrc #childtrafficking

So far this year, Michigan has reported 74 cases of human trafficking. It is a big problem in the state and it happens every day, every where and involves people you would never suspect. #humantrafficking
Sex trafficking survivors said these three steps can help stop sex trafficking: 1) Educate the public 2) Increase penalties for "buyers" 3) Recognize the signs and risks

Kevin Kimmel, an alert trucker called the police after he saw something disturbing at the truck stop.  That call ended weeks of torture, starvation and forced prostitution for the victim. Because of truckers like Kimmel and Truckers Against Trafficking there is an increased awareness and may victims have been rescued.
A Nebraska sex trafficking report released by the Women's Fund of Omaha indicates there is a "woeful lack of awareness" across the state about the crime. http://buff.ly/29TA1Yl #childtrafficking

"Unfortunately, more gangs are expanding from traditional pursuits like drug dealing into this lucrative business," says US Attorney Laura Duffy. "These gangsters are preying upon our youth, and we are using every law enforcement resource to keep our children and our communities safe from these predators." http://buff.ly/29K2VWG #childtrafficking
A phone call from an alert citizen lead to the arrest of a trafficker who was selling a 15 yr old girl for sex.  If you see something, say something. http://buff.ly/2a6oyTr #childtrafficking

Sex trafficking victims are often moved from city to city so they remain unfamiliar with their surroundings and are less likely to escape. It also keeps the girls "fresh and new" to buyers scrolling through sex websites says Carl Waterstreet, a Wisconsin Department of Justice special agent.

A Nebraska study aimed at giving sex trafficking survivors a voice brought to light many issues.  One shocking issue says Dr. Shireen Rajaram is victims are being trafficking by their own parents, boyfriends, and fathers.  Often times drugs were involved. http://buff.ly/2a0WeSo #childtrafficking

Students need to know the facts about child sex trafficking.  They need to be able to recognize the signs and know where to go for help if it is happening to them or a friend.  Education is power. http://buff.ly/29KI07x #childtrafficking

Five disguises human traffickers use to gain a victim's trust:  Pretender, Provider, Promiser, Protector and Punisher. Once they gain trust, the exploitation begins.  http://buff.ly/29DehMh #childtrafficking

"Sadly, domestic trafficking is not uncommon in South Carolina - we have to raise awareness to keep kids safe," social worker Carla Damron said. "A child advertised as being available for 're-homing' would have great appeal to traffickers. #childtrafficking  "

If you have kids you have probably heard of Pokmon Go, you may even be playing it yourself. While the game is fun and gets your kids outside, it comes with some real dangers that you and your child need to be aware of.  http://buff.ly/29SJ2T2 #childtrafficking

Brazilian cops rescue 8 kids from sex trafficking ring near Rio Olympic site. Big events, like the Olympics, unfortunately mean a rise in human trafficking in the area.  http://buff.ly/29C471f #childtrafficking
#SavingTheGirlNextDoor is a proposed bill in Canada aimed at stopping child trafficking, which is on the rise in Canada.  http://buff.ly/29Gu40b #childtrafficking

"While law enforcement is important, so is providing adequate support for trafficking victims' recovery. And, in that regard, we are failing. We are failing because we have not identified human trafficking as the public health issue it is. You see, trafficking is not a short-term affliction-it affects a survivor's whole life, families and even entire communities," says survivor Margeaux Gray.

"Victims are completely without resources," according to Roxann Ryan. "They are afraid and usually, they've been separated from their family and their friends and the need for services is tremendous." #Humantrafficking

If you are shoppping the great deals during #PrimeDay, Amazon will donate to Erase Child Trafficking if you shop through our AmazonSmile link below.  Thank you for your support in ending child trafficking. http://amzn.to/29Nzm8S

"With the realization that just because a certain abuse has taken place in the past doesn't mean that we have to tolerate that abuse in the future or that we can afford to avert our eyes. Instead, we should be asking ourselves - what if that victim of trafficking was my daughter, son, sister, or brother?" - Sec of State John Kerry http://buff.ly/29ykiud #humantrafficking

UVM is the first facility to use simulation as a training too to help professionals recognize the warning signs of human trafficking.  The program will likely be used as an education model for hospitals around the country. http://buff.ly/29Dc72r #humantrafficking
We need to remember that women can be traffickers too. In this case, these two women trafficked a 15 year old girl under the escort section of Backpage.  http://buff.ly/29u6WV8 #childtrafficking

This is a difficult story to read, but it makes an important point. We don't talk enough about how people with mental and physical disabilities are especially vulnerable to the risks of human trafficking.  We need to have safeguards in place to protect them too. http://buff.ly/29tzI2O #humantrafficking

It's great to see positive things like this happening in the courts.  A new court in Miami-Dade was formed to deal specifically with teen victims of sex trafficking. It will provide "comprehensive services and support" to victims & their families, http://buff.ly/29yBDpC #childtrafficking

Law enforcement is relied upon every day to protect us as citizens. Sadly, their job is often taken for granted. We at ERASE have great respect for law enforcement, we see the work they do to save and protect child trafficking victims. We are deeply saddened by the deaths and injuries of the officers in Dallas and ask that you keep them and their families in your thoughts and prayers.
"No little girl dreams that they want to be human trafficked and used as a sex slave. There's no little girl that does that," says sex trafficking survivor Kathy Jackson #humantrafficking
It is our mission to change the way people perceive child trafficking. Making light of a serious topic only hurts the victims. http://buff.ly/29Sbq3h #childtrafficking

"One may think that sex trafficking only happens in under-developed neighborhoods, or only in other countries. Indiana Attorney General Greg Zoeller reiterates that is simply not true, as it happens in any neighborhood, and from any computer or phone" via ABC News

New Indiana laws expand definition of sex offenders to include child traffickers and allows the Department of Child Services to help a child who is living with an adult who is involved with sex trafficking.  http://buff.ly/29lden6 #childtrafficking

New Michigan law requires human trafficking notices be posted in airports, bus and train stations, rest stops and strip clubs.  The signs tell them to call the National Human Trafficking Resource Center. http://buff.ly/29hrmLl #humantrafficking

"Human trafficking is a huge part of the (Sturges) motorcycle rally that nobody wants to talk about," says Tammie Brock. She adds that campgrounds should be trained in the signs of human trafficking "http://buff.ly/29kKwUk #childtrafficking

While celebrating our country's 240th Independence day  with our friends and families, please take a moment to reflect on the 46 children who are taken from their families today and the 17,000 children this year who will have their independence taken from them.
Man lures 14 year old middle school girl using snapchat. Parents, please take the time to talk to your kids about internet safety.

Advocate Carla Tweddale says "The average age of entry into human trafficking is 11-13 for boys and 12-14 for girls. Eighty percent of sex-trafficking victims are female. Children and teens who have run away from home are likely to be victimized - 1 in 6 United States runaways become sex-trafficking victims. But traffickers can also find their victims on school campuses, feigning romantic interest to teens who don't feel like they fit."  http://buff.ly/298nZJy #childtrafficking

"This is a widespread problem in Tennessee, and is especially disturbing as many victims of human trafficking are children," said Senator Overbey.  "These predators target Tennessee's most vulnerable, That is why it is so important to strengthen penalties against those who exploit them"

San Diego County says it is time to talk about the "Ugly Truth" of sex trafficking.  The FBI has classified San Diego as a "High Intensity Child Prostitution Area" on a list of top 13 cities for prostituting children. A recent study by the UCSD and Point Loma Nazarene University says the average age for entry into sex trafficking is 16 years old. http://buff.ly/290qw5e  #ChildTrafficking

Ambassador Susan Coppedge says we need to stop criminalizing the victims of human trafficking  so they have a better chance at starting a new life.  With an arrest record it is hard for them to get housing and jobs to begin the process of starting over.  http://buff.ly/291IebY #humantrafficking

Wisconsin Attorney General Brad Schimel said human trafficking is a serious problem and it is going to be one of the toughest social services and criminal justice challenges.  "Our biggest challenge is just getting victims to agree to be rescued," Schimel said. Traffickers do such extensive emotional manipulation of their victims. http://buff.ly/28YQs6Z #humantrafficking

Contra Costa Grand Jury report say "Placing the child in juvenile hall on a criminal charge runs the risk of exposing the child to criminal behavior. Once in juvenile hall, most victims of (sex trafficking) are uncooperative and ultimately released back to their next of kin, where they will likely walk back to their exploiters."
Take time to talk to your children this weekend about internet safety.  It's a conversation you will be glad you had.
We are honored to be a part of this great community event tonight. Thank you to the Wilcox Foundation & Gallery for inviting us.

New York State Attorney General Eric Schneiderman says there are areas of New York where human trafficking laws are simply not being used. Counties like Schenectady & Saratoga have never reported a sex trafficking arrest.  #humantrafficking #childtrafficking
Six important tips to keep your children safe from online predators and child traffickers
St. Paul Police Chief Todd Axtell says,  "The more systems we have in place to support those who are being prostituted and human trafficked the more effective we'll be in combating this crime."

Something as simple as taking a few photos of your hotel room could help stop child sex trafficking. The photos, which are uploaded to the app TraffickCam help law enforcement determine which hotels victims are being held at.   #HelpErase #childtrafficking

It is a myth that human trafficking victims are hidden away from plain sight.  Often times they come in contact with every day people but are too afraid to talk.  They have been told if they tell anyone they won't be believed, they will be arrested, their families will never accept them, or in worse cases, they or their families will be harmed or killed.   This is why education is important.  We need to learn to recognize the signs of human trafficking and if we suspect something, we need to contact local authorities.  Once call can save a life.

A bill proposed by Laurie Scott called "Saving the Girl Next Door" would allow sex trafficking victims to bring their captors to justice through restraining orders and the ability to sue them for damages.

Today is #WorldRefugeeDay and we want to repost this important article about the exploitation refugee children are facing. Refugee children are deliberately separated from their parents by smugglers so they can be exploited; they are seldom reported as missing. In response to this increasing problem, 30 European organizations are coming together to help these children. #childtrafficking #human trafficking http://bit.ly/1Yo4Rdh

New York State Attorney General Eric Schneiderman says there are areas of New York where human trafficking laws are simply not being used. Counties like Schenectady & Saratoga have never reported a sex trafficking arrest.  #humantrafficking #childtrafficking
Happy Father's Day! Go have fun today!

We would like to acknowledge Kim and Jeff Love of Big Fish DPI - Jeff Love.  The Loves have joined forces with ERASE Child Trafficking and  Phantom Rescue to stop the abduction of children for the sex trafficking industry.  Kim spends endless hours assisting and applying for grants and assistance.  Her efforts resulted in great success when Henry Schein Cares Foundation (HSC) provided us with over 400 Individual Care Packets.  We are grateful that companies like Henry Schein Dental establish foundations that have a commitment to social responsibility. Their mission is to expand access to health care for underserved & at-risk populations.  Thank you for being Heroes in the fight against child trafficking.

message: Take a moment to look at some of the common signs #HumanTrafficking victims display.

"The worst truth that I've learned is that the villains are more equipped than the heroes...and there are more of them because we're comfortable pretending nothing's happening" says Ryan Anderson Bell about child/human trafficking.  As a father himself he says this discussion needs to be brought to the forefront for the safety of our children.  #HelpErase #childtrafficking

Lisa Arnold, director of the movie "Caged No More" says, "I can't tell you how many survivors I've talked with that their parents were responsible for them being trafficked. Many in the U.S. are being trafficked daily in their home and then they go to school and their school has no idea. It's being done by the people that should be caring for them the most."  Tony Sparks, founder of Phantom Rescue says sex trafficking is becoming so rampant that it is passing the war on drugs.  Traffickers realize a bag go drugs can only be sold once, but a child or woman can be sold 30 times a day or more. http://buff.ly/1Op4Vr1 #HelpErase #Childtrafficking

Kentucky is talking about their sex trafficking problem.  In Louisville alone, each day there are about 100 ads on a single website involving sex trafficking.  Sex trafficking makes up 78% of their human trafficking cases, and 60% of the victims are children.  #HelpErase #Childtrafficking

People like Merlin Global Services CEO Brian Raduenz, have not only helped us raise money for our organization, but have helped us raise awareness about child trafficking in this country.    All it takes is for one person like Brian to start a conversation, and soon you will have several more people talking about it.  Thank you again Brian for being a hero in our community.  http://bit.ly/1W4RJcC #childtrafficking #HelpErase

Refugee children are deliberately separated from their parents by smugglers so they can be exploited; they are seldom reported as missing.  In response to this increasing problem, 30 European organizations are coming together to help these children.  #childtrafficking #humantrafficking
Nebraska is preparing for a major clamp down on #humantrafficking, but advocates say that the state needs to do more for survivors when it comes to housing, counseling and medical care

Another too familiar case where a minor is given drugs and alcohol and forced into sex trafficking.  Luckily this 15 year old girl escaped and her traffickers are facing charges.  She says she would be moved from hotel to hotel and be forced to have sex with as many as 10 men each day. #childtrafficking #HelpErase
Our thoughts and prayers are with the victims and families involved in the horrific Florida shooting.  [brokenheart]

Talk to your kids about internet safety. Predators are looking for children who are vulnerable online. Education means empowerment.  Remind them that anyone can be behind an internet handle.  #childtrafficking #HelpErase

In the first 48 hours of being on the street, 1 in 3 runaways can be lured into child sex trafficking. It's important we have places like YMCA Safe Place locations for them to go to seek help. #childtrafficking  http://bit.ly/28pZ5fi

The Eau Claire, Wisconsin school district is taking a proactive approach to child exploitation. They say it is time to educate the students, staff and community about human trafficking / child trafficking

A female solider at Ft. Bragg has been a victim of sex trafficking - not once, but twice.  As a minor she was exploited and recently she became a victim again at the age of 19.  The man threatened to report her to her commander if she stopped. This is another example of the importance of proper aftercare if a victim has any hope of reclaiming their life. We need to remember that getting them out is just the first step in their recovery.

At 8 years old Elisabeth Corey was forced into sex trafficking by her own family.  When she wasn't forced to work bachelor parties or have encounters with men, she attended school and played with her friends. This is an example of why we need to make sure people are educated about what child trafficking looks like.  It's in your community, your child's friend could be a victim. Learn the facts. EraseChildTraffickingorg #HelpErase #ChildTrafficking  http://bit.ly/1PAVYuT

This man used Instagram to get a young girl to friend him and send him photos. He also attempted to arrange for a personal meet up to give her "prize money" she had won.  Parents take note, talk to your children, have an internet safety plan. #HelpErase #childtrafficking http://bit.ly/25FBuVR

During summer, kids spend more time online.  Now is the time to familiarize yourself with apps that are popular with teens, talk to them about Internet safety and put a plan in place in the event they encounter something that makes them uncomfortable online.

Often times we forget to talk about the positive outcomes for victims of #childtrafficking. Although their experiences are terrible, with the proper aftercare and support, they can go on to reclaim their lives and have a bright future.  We would like to congratulate this young woman on her recent high school graduation and recognize Mollie's House who gave her the care and support she needed.  #HelpErase http://bit.ly/1XphK7R

Do you know about these 7 dangerous apps?  Your tweens &  teens probably do.  As parents we need to be aware of them in order to help keep our children safe from online predators. #HelpErase #Childtrafficking http://buff.ly/1ZgLxwO

Sandra Woworunthu is a human trafficking / sex trafficking survivor.  Her story is powerful and should be a wakeup call to everyone. What is happening to these victims is horrific. We need to work together to put an end to human trafficking and make sure victims get the help they need to reclaim their lives. This article is a call to action.  #HelpErase #humantrafficking

The internet allows traffickers to connect to children they may never have otherwise met. It also lets them reach into small towns they normally wouldn't travel to, according to FBI agent Ted Docks. The victim in this story was using the apps Whisper and Kik. buff.ly/1Vz4FHb
Michigan State Attorney General Bill Schuette says the state is trying to take a victim centered approach to human trafficking.  His efforts have allowed victim's criminal records to be expunged.

With summer approaching, the online risk for children increases as they have more time to spend online.  The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation says now is the time to talk to your children about online safety and create a plan if an encounter online makes them uncomfortable. #childtrafficking #HelpErase http://bit.ly/1UhMgcu

If you suspect child trafficking is taking place, you should call your local police.  Major David Dalton of the Clearwater Police Department says they would rather investigate a tip that may not turn out to human trafficking than not receive a tip that may have helped rescue a victim. http://bit.ly/1VwbTfa

Canadian based Voice Found CEO, Cynthia Bland says, "When you've been spending your time manipulated - and it is a mind and emotional manipulation - you get to a place where you believe that you really are not worthy. You're a commodity being sold, and so there is shame attached to that and trauma."  http://bit.ly/1TViUUf #HelpErase #childtrafficking

message: This is why we stress the importance of proper, professional aftercare for child sex trafficking victims. Large cities in Louisiana like New Orleans, Shreveport and Baton Rouge are seeing a growing problem with child sex trafficking.  The more we talk about the problem, the better is becomes.  We never want to think that a parent or family member could sell a child into sex trafficking (we like to think it's just strangers who do it), but, the sooner we face the harsh facts of child trafficking, the more children we can protect. For more information on child trafficking in our country, visit our website at www.EraseChildTrafficking.org  http://bit.ly/1SZ3lvK

A very heartbreaking story around Mother's Day, but it's an important one to share because unfortunately without proper aftercare, child victims of #sextrafficking can easily be lured back.  It's important we have safe facilities for them to go to as they reclaim their lives. We work with several great facilities, unfortunately the problem is so big that their aren't enough safe facilities to house them. We all need to work together to ensure that once a child is rescued that they have a safe place to heal both physically and mentally.  Please visit us at EraseChildTrafficking.org for more information.  http://cbsloc.al/1q6xg9y
Having a safe home for victims of human trafficking is a key part of their recovery.

Coming forward is often difficult for victims of #sextrafficking.  That is why it is important that we make sure we have programs in place to support them as they recover and reclaim their lives.  They have not only suffered physically, but they have suffered emotionally. Breaking the cycle can be hard, but with compassionate, professional help available, the process is easier.  #childtrafficking #HelpErase http://bit.ly/1TMXSa4

According to the NY Times yesterday, "more than a million migrants having reached Europe in the last year and many more on the way, NATO stepped into the crisis for the first time on Thursday, saying it would deploy ships to the Aegean Sea in an attempt to stop smugglers."   Refugees, especially women and children, smuggled into Europe have become targets for sex traffickers.
